1 (2) Requires the parent with whom the child resists contact
2 to take action to remediate the resistance of the child as a
3 condition precedent to requiring the other parent of the child to
4 take any action to improve the relationship of the child with the
5 parent with whom the child resists contact.
6 2. For the purposes of this section, an order or injunction is
7 in the nature of a temporary or extended order for protection if it
8 grants relief that might be given in a temporary or extended order
9 for protection.
10 3. As used in this section:
11 (a) “Child abuse” means:
12 (1) Physical or mental injury of a nonaccidental nature to a
13 child under the age of 18 years; or
14 (2) Sexual abuse or sexual exploitation of a child under the
15 age of 18 years.
16 (b) “Clinical experience” means experience working with and
17 on behalf of victims of domestic violence or child abuse.
18 (c) “Forensic” means provided pursuant to a court order for
19 the purpose of litigation. The term includes, without limitation, the
20 evaluation of a parent or child involved in a child custody
21 proceeding.
22 (d) “Order for protection” means:
23 (1) A temporary or extended order for protection against
24 domestic violence issued pursuant to NRS 33.017 to 33.100,
25 inclusive;
26 (2) A temporary or extended order for protection against
27 stalking, aggravated stalking or harassment issued pursuant to
28 NRS 200.591; or
29 (3) A temporary or extended order for protection against
30 sexual assault issued pursuant to NRS 200.378.
31 (e) “Sexual abuse” has the meaning ascribed to it in
32 NRS 432B.100.
33 (f) “Sexual exploitation” has the meaning ascribed to it in
34 NRS 432B.110.
35 Sec. 7. 1. Any judge who presides over a child custody
36 proceeding and any person who, during the scope of his or her
37 employment, has regular and routine contact with persons who
38 are involved in a child custody proceeding, including, without
39 limitation, any guardian ad litem, attorney appointed by the court
40 to represent a child, custody evaluator, mediator or employee of
41 the court, shall, in addition to any other required training,
42 complete training relating to domestic violence and child abuse.
43 2. The training required by subsection 1 must comply with
44 the applicable requirements of the Violence Against Women Act
